description:
Next, in this episode we take a look into the French Reformation. Developed in the 16th century in Paris, France, it certainly wasn't an easy ride. There was strong tension and conflict between the Protestants and Catholics. Progress on the Reformation lost its brightest minds to other countries, at best and at worst, to death and persecution.

To find out more about this episode please read our extended article with extra facts and references.
